#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Eskom and other State Owned Entities (SEO) are looking into policy changes regarding scrapyards. This follows the scourge of cable theft, with the proceeds often ending up in these places. South African Police Service, Johannesburg Metro Police Deparrtment and Eskom recently joined forces to raid a Devland scrapyard near Soweto. READ: Cable theft | Major bust near Soweto The cables they confiscated were stolen from Transnet Freight Rail, Prasa, Eskom and City Power. Eskom Head of security, Karen Pillay says the power utility is putting measures in place to curb this economic sabotage. Watch the video above for more details on this story.